rComments: Very good at teaching this course. Pay careful attention to his jokes, they're actually kind of funny. Informative, and overall high quality professor at UofT.
Excellent in details of all course material. One of the best professor I had in the finance classes.

not the worse but there are definetly better options for professors to have if your taking finance. his notes are incomplete and his lectures are hard to follow because your trying to follow what hes saying while filling out the notes. he definetly doesnt i know its not all his fault, but the tests are really hard, lots of trick questions
He's good. He is actually able to interest you in the course, which is (admit it!) pretty hard considering it's rather dry...
Very Good prof, covers materials in class well and thoroughly, is also helpful during office hours. Tests and exams are a bit hard though, u have to prepare well for them.
Take this course with him! He is one of the rare instructors in the commerce program who actually teaches the material in class. Do what you can to get his section. Trust me on this one.
He's a great prof, nice and helpful and very considerate. Great teaching that makes the course a lot easier
